---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="About | Full Product Dev"
  description="Learn about Patrick Robinson and Full Product Dev's mission to help developers build products that actually matter."
>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="article-content" style="max-width: 65ch; margin: 0 auto;">
      <header style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        <div style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <img 
            src="/profile-pic.jpeg" 
            alt="Patrick Robinson" 
            style="
              width: 150px; 
              height: 150px; 
              border-radius: 50%; 
              object-fit: cover; 
              margin: 0 auto; 
              display: block;
              box-shadow: 0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
              border: 4px solid var(--primary-100);
            "
          />
        </div>
        <h1>About Full Product Dev</h1>
        <p style="font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
          Building the right thing, not just building it right
        </p>
      </header>

      <section style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7;">
          Hi, I'm Patrick Robinson—a software developer with over a decade of experience and a growing obsession with building products that actually matter.
        </p>
        
        <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7;">
          Full Product Dev is a space for developers who care about more than code quality (though that's important too). It's for those of us who ask, "Should we build this?" before we ask, "How fast can we ship it?"
        </p>
        
        <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7;">
          I write about being product-minded as a developer—working at the intersection of engineering, design, and user value. This blog exists to explore what it means to build the right thing, not just build it right.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        <h2>What Full Product Dev Covers</h2>
        <div style="display: grid; gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 2rem;">
          <div style="padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--bg-secondary); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: var(--radius-lg);">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--primary-600);">Product-Minded Development</h3>
            <p style="margin: 0;">Understanding user needs and building features that drive real impact, not just checking boxes.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div style="padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--bg-secondary); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: var(--radius-lg);">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--primary-600);">Engineering Excellence</h3>
            <p style="margin: 0;">Best practices for writing clean, scalable code that serves users and stands the test of time.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div style="padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--bg-secondary); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: var(--radius-lg);">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: var(--primary-600);">Cross-Functional Collaboration</h3>
            <p style="margin: 0;">Building bridges between engineering, product, and design for better outcomes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        <h2>Why Full Product Dev Exists</h2>
        <p>
          Too many developers focus solely on the "how" of building software without questioning the "why" or "what." 
          Full Product Dev exists to bridge that gap—helping developers think like product owners while maintaining 
          their engineering rigor.
        </p>
        
        <p>
          The best products come from developers who understand users, collaborate effectively with non-technical 
          teammates, and make thoughtful trade-offs between technical excellence and user value.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Core Principles:</h3>
        <ul style="margin-top: 1rem;">
          <li><strong>User value first</strong> - Every technical decision should consider the user impact</li>
          <li><strong>Question everything</strong> - "Should we build this?" comes before "How do we build this?"</li>
          <li><strong>Quality with purpose</strong> - Build great code that solves real problems</li>
          <li><strong>Collaborative mindset</strong> - Great products require great teamwork across disciplines</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section style="text-align: center; padding: 2rem; background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--primary-50) 0%, var(--bg-secondary) 100%); border-radius: var(--radius-xl); margin-top: 3rem;">
        <h2 style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Join the Conversation</h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
          Ready to become a more product-minded developer? Start by exploring Full Product Dev's 
          latest articles and join the conversation about building software that matters.
        </p>
        <a href="/blog" class="hero-cta">
          Read the Blog
        </a>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
